                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>1998-04-01</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>I had the displeasure of having to read this book for a research paper assignment in my U.S. History class, but was soon quite surprised.  In fact, Sitkoff presented the civil rights struggle in an extremely interesting way, and I thouroughly enjoyed the experience.  What began as a bothersome paper assignment became one of the best books I have read in a long time.END</span>
                  
              
